  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Algorithm
    This interface is use to set the infrastructure for all Algorithm types
    AlgorithmController
    This is the master controller in the MVC pattern It will handle the Observer pasterns between the GUI and Model with the Action listeners It will also handle the creation of all the Models and Views
    AlgorithmResult
    Simple class to represent the data to be collected when comparing Algorithms
    AlgorithmStatModel
    Class to represent the model to compare the different algorithms.
    AStar
    This Algorithm will implment the A* path finding method.
    BFS
    Implementation of Breadth First Search
    DFS
    Implementation of Depth First Search
    GridModel
    This class is used to represent the Model for a 2d graph.
    GridTile
    This class is to represent the base tile in a Grid Model.
    GridView
    This is the View where the main visualization of the Grid will be used
    GUIView
    This is the main View that all the base components are created and positioned.
    Path  
    Simulation
    This class is responsible for running the simulation against the different Algorithm.
    Tile
    Base of the GridTile to implemnt a basic 2d point on a grid
